It seems that challenges in this regard have already begun to显现. Due to the FAA's stance on certain drugs, I may find it difficult to obtain my medical certificate.
This is not impossible, but it would require a great deal of time and entail a lot of additional work.
Although this is somewhat discouraging, it merely adds another problem to be solved, and currently it does seem "truly" solvable. It just requires a significant amount of time and money.
If you want to know what challenges lie ahead for me:
The FAA doesn't like ADHD. If you are taking medication for ADHD, you definitely won't get a medical certificate.
